               <msContents>
                  <summary>Nerses IV's Commentary on Matthew, etc., 17th cent.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item1" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 2</locus>
                     <author>Nersēs, Shnorhali, Saint, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1102" to="1173">1102 - 1173</date>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">Sermon on the grade and the staff of Vardapets, on text Ps.CX.2.</title>
                     <incipit>Թէ վասն ե՛ր գաւազանն զարդարելոյն արտաքս բերէ: Պխ. վասն բազում պատճառաց. նախ զի …</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item2" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 8</locus>
                     <author>Nersēs, Shnorhali, Saint, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1102" to="1173">1102 - 1173</date>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">Explanation of the framework of the Eusebian Canons of Gospels.</title>
                     <title xml:lang="hy">Մեկնութիւն խորանաց աւետարանին.</title>
                     <incipit>Մատեանք ա՟ծագիծք և հոգէբուղխ վդ՟տութի՟ք իմաստից …</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item3" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 13</locus>
                     <author>Nersēs, Shnorhali, Saint, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1102" to="1173">1102 - 1173</date>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">'From the ecclesiastical history;, dealing with the question, Why the Gospels are written, and how?</title>
                     <incipit>Առաքեալք բ՟ժան և այլ աշակերտք հբ՟ …</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item4" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 15</locus>
                     <author>Nersēs, Shnorhali, Saint, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1102" to="1173">1102 - 1173</date>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Matthew, by Nerses Shnorhali, with the continuation by John of Erzenka.</title>
                     <incipit>Սրիոյ զաւրութիւն գերազանց է քան զբնութիւն, և այն քան մինչ զի մոռացումն առնել տկարութեան …</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                     <note>This commentary, being mostly an abridged compilation of John Chrysosto, is divided like its original in the Armenian translation, into four books, and curiously the titles of theses division in this MS bear the name, not of John of Erzenka, but of St. John Chrysostom.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item5" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 214</locus>
                     <author>Matthew Vardapet</author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">Commenrary on the six days of the Creation, by Matthew Vardapet</title>
                     <incipit>Սքանշելի են գործք ƒո և անձն իմ սիրեաց յոյժ …</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item6" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 280</locus>
                     <author>Matthew Vardapet</author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">On eight evil thoughts, by Matthew Vardapet, compuled from the Doctrine [Antirrheticus] of Evagrius Ponticus, 'who is called the Mind of the deser, and from his follower St. Nilus'.</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                     <note>Contains: On Gluttony; On Fornication; On Avarice; On Sadness; On Wrath; on Melancholy; On Vainglory; On Pride. It ends with a memorial of the author, telling that he has finished 'this compendium in the inner hermitage (անապատ) of Tantzapharakh' (Տանծափարախ) in Siunik, East Armenia, in 1393.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item7" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 303</locus>
                     <author>Nersēs, Shnorhali, Saint, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1102" to="1173">1102 - 1173</date>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">An epitome on Genesis</title>
                     <title xml:lang="hy">Յաղագս արարածոց համառօտ</title>
                     <incipit>Արար ա՟ծ զմարդն ի պատկեր իւր …</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                     <note>It deals with some quesions per saltum, beginning from the creation of man, and extending as far as the New Testament. All in form of question and answer.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Arm_e_15-item8" n="1">
                     <locus>f. 310</locus>
                     <author>Nersēs, Shnorhali, Saint, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1102" to="1173">1102 - 1173</date>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">Extracts from the Book of Questions</title>
                     <title xml:lang="hy">Ի Հարցողաց գրոց</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="hy">Armenian</textLang>
                     <note>I.e. the Monastic Rules of St. Basil.</note>
                  </msItem>
